# C-HashMap — Hash Map Library in C

This project contains an implementation of a dynamic hash map using chaining to handle collisions.  
Keys are strings, values are `void*`, allowing the structure to store any type.

## Features
- Insert key-value pairs  
- Retrieve values by key  
- Delete keys  
- Check key existence  
- djb2 hashing function  
- Collision handling using linked lists  

## Demo Program
The demo application reads words from `input.txt` and counts their frequencies using the hash map.

